-- CTC Media’s Moscow Audience Falls in Week to May 13, TNS Says
-- B y   H a l i a   P a v l i v a
-- 2012-05-15T19:18:26Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-05-15/ctc-media-s-moscow-audience-falls-in-week-to-may-13-tns-says.html
CTC Media Inc. (CTCM) ’s average daily share
of viewers in Moscow aged 18-years-old and above fell to 5.7
percent in the week to May 13, data compiled by TNS-Global show.  The share of viewers in Moscow for the CTC TV channel, the
Nasdaq-listed Russian media company’s biggest source of revenue,
fell from 6.4 percent in the week to May 6, data researcher TNS-
Global said in an e-mail today. Pervyi Kanal, NTV Television,
Rossiya-1, TNT and REN TV all ranked ahead of CTC among Moscow
viewers, TNS-Global data show.  The average daily audience among viewers four-years-old and
over in Moscow for CTC fell to 6.3 percent in the week to May 13
from 7.3 percent in the previous week, knocking it down one
level in the audience rankings, the data show. CTC came out
sixth in this category of viewers in the week to May 13, while
Pervyi Kanal, NTV Television, Rossiya-1, TNT and REN TV all
ranked ahead of CTC, TNS-Global said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
